### Affected Package
@angular/common/http/testing


### Is this a regression?
unknown


### Description
Because of unit test,I test http request with HttpClientTestingModule.
But the when the body is json and header-`Content-Type` not `application/json`,
I get the `TestRequest` instance by`httpTestingController.expectOne('xxx')`
the testQuest.request's body is also origin not convert



## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
`Content-Type` is `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` so body must as string like` { p1: 1, p2: 2 }`,but `req.request.body` also a object
```ts
  it('origin', async (done) => {
    http.post('http://127.0.0.1:3000/aaa', { p1: 1, p2: 2 }, {
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
      }
    }).subscribe((val) => {
      done()
    })
    let req = httpTestingController.expectOne('http://127.0.0.1:3000/aaa');
    req.event(new HttpResponse({ body: { c: 'retrun' }, status: 200 }))
  })
```
## üî• Exception or Error
the body we assign shoud auto convert with `Content-Type`



